    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Class III VAD hemolysis prediction domain",
      "description": "Applicable to centrifugal blood pumps operating as long-term ventricular assist devices in adult patients. Scope is limited to Newtonian blood rheology models with hematocrit 35–45%, inlet flow rates 3–8 L/min, and impeller speeds 2000–3500 RPM. Predictions of hemolysis index (HI) must be compared against absolute clinical thresholds; relative comparisons to predicate devices are out of scope for this COU."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
