        "description": "Solver must demonstrate second-order spatial convergence on the Taylor-Green vortex and lid-driven cavity benchmarks. Order of accuracy must be verified via Richardson extrapolation with at least three systematically refined meshes. Hemolysis transport scalar must achieve first-order temporal convergence."
      },
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation on three systematically refined meshes (1.2M, 4.8M, 19.2M cells) confirms second-order spatial convergence (observed order p=1.94) for velocity and pressure fields. Hemolysis scalar transport achieves first-order temporal convergence as expected for the implicit Euler scheme. Taylor-Green vortex benchmark matches analytical solution to within 0.3% at t=1s. Achieved Gradation 5: formal order-of-accuracy study with three mesh levels, benchmark comparison, and documented convergence certificates."
