        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The turbulence model must be justified for swirling confined flows with adverse pressure gradients. The hemolysis power-law coefficients must be sourced from peer-reviewed literature with documented experimental basis. Non-Newtonian blood rheology effects must be assessed and documented as either included or justified as negligible."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on documented superior performance for swirling flows with adverse pressure gradients (Menter 1994; Hariharan 2011 benchmark). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis coefficients (α=3.62×10⁻⁷, β=2.416, γ=0.785) sourced from Giersiepen et al. (1990) with supporting validation in Goubergrits & Affeld (2004). Non-Newtonian effects assessed: at shear rates >100 s⁻¹ (dominant in pump), Newtonian approximation introduces <3% viscosity error — documented as negligible. Achieved Gradation 4: justified turbulence model, peer-reviewed hemolysis coefficients, documented non-Newtonian assessment."
